The Smart Crop Advisory System for Small and Marginal Farmers is a technology-driven solution designed to support farmers in making informed agricultural decisions. 
The system uses data such as soil conditions, weather information, and crop requirements to provide suitable recommendations for crop selection, irrigation, fertilizer application, and pest management.
By integrating technologies like Artificial Intelligence, data analytics, and mobile applications, the system delivers timely and accurate advice to farmers. 
This helps improve crop productivity, reduce farming costs, and minimize crop losses caused by unpredictable environmental conditions.
The system is especially beneficial for small and marginal farmers who have limited access to agricultural experts and modern farming knowledge.
Overall, the Smart Crop Advisory System promotes efficient resource utilization and supports sustainable agricultural practices. 
